      "content": "Originalists argue that the Constitution was designed to endure across generations, and therefore, ignoring societal shifts is not a flaw but a feature of the system. They contend that if the Framers intended the text to evolve with culture, they would have written it that way, yet the text remains fixed to prevent the judiciary from becoming a super-legislature. This method actually protects minority rights by locking in the original promises made to all citizens, rather than allowing the majority's temporary passions to dictate constitutional law.",
