    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i get the theory, but it feels kind of impossible to ever truly know what \"original public meaning\" was 200 years ago without just projecting what we want onto it. isn't it more realistic to say that modern judges use originalism as a shield to justify conclusions they've already reached for political reasons? like, why should we treat it as a legitimate legal framework instead of just a sophisticated way to do politics?",
